               <p>THOMAS COURTNEY. I am a <rs id="t18300415-290-viclabel1583" type="occupation">cheesemonger</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18300415-290-victim2461 t18300415-290-viclabel1583"></join>, and live in <placeName id="t18300415-290-crimeloc1584">Drury-lane</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18300415-290-crimeloc1584" type="placeName" value="Drury-lane"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18300415-290-crimeloc1584" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18300415-290-off1581 t18300415-290-crimeloc1584"></join>. On the 20th of March I lost a ham, about half-past eleven o'clock at night - I did not see it taken, but the Policeman brought it back, and I believe it to be mine; I had had it in my hand twice that day - I do not see any difference between this and mine; it is the same weight and size.</p>

               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18300415-290-person2462">
                  JOHN 
                  RAWLEY
               <interp inst="t18300415-290-person2462" type="surname" value="RAWLEY"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18300415-290-person2462" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18300415-290-person2462" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I stopped the prisoner on suspicion, three or four hundred yards from the shop, with this ham under his arm - I asked where he got it; he said at a shop leading to Clare-market, which is the prosecutor's - I lodged him in the watch-house, and took the ham to the shop; he said he bought it at 5 1/2d. per lb., and it weighed 10 1/4lbs., but it weighs 12 1/4lbs. - he was going from the shop.</p>
               <p>Prisoner. I said 6d. per pound.</p>
               <p>THOMAS COURTNEY. It would have been 7d. per pound.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I saw this ham and asked the price - they said 7d. per pound; I said I would give 6d. for the whole, and it was weighed to me - it weighed 10 1/2lbs., and I gave 5s. 1 1/2d. for it.</p>
               <p>JURY to JOHN RAWLEY. Q. Had he any money on him? A. He stated that he had none, but I believe he was not searched.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t18300415-290-verdict1585" type="verdictDescription">
